Ie: The players computer controls who gets what items, etc.<br>
<br>
EverQuest is a game who's core functions were are server side.<br>
Ie: The EverQuest server controls what happens to your character, and typically ingores any data sent by your client that it considers invalid.<br>
<br>
There's a few exceptions, and some other functions that it will let the client have more control over, but essentially if you try to &quot;hack&quot; your client's memory to say that you're invincible, you still die in the game world once you've taken XX damage, and get sent to your bindpoint. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Most item dupe bugs in EverQuest exploit coding flaws on the server in regards to how it transfers items around. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365" target="top">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=279732" target="top">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=itsastony>itsastony</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 4:20:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=454.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Client Side vs Server Side</span><hr size=1> I would be very interested in knowing how much cheating is really possible in EQ. Not to cheat myself - thats why I dont want to know how it works - just to know if I am still playing in a world in which everyone has the same chances.<br>
