<br>
This is more of what I'm talking about.<br>
<br>
I'm not talkin about dupe bugs or anything like that, I mean if you stumble across something that helps you, would you report it and use it, just report it, or not report it and use it?<br>
<br>
If you die from going LD because of a server issue on SOE's end, you don't get 100%exp rez (under most circumstances).<br>
<br>
If you drown because you cast an eye of zomm and the game considers you underwater, you won't get 100%exp rez (again under most circumstances).<br>
<br>
If you are trying to complete a quest and the mob takes your items and doesn't give you the next parts back and can't prove beyond any doubt that you did lose the items, you are the one whom loses.<br>
<br>
All these negative things that could (and do) happen yet SOE feels that this is 'part of the game' and we have to live with it.<br>
<br>
Yet the second we find something that benefits us (whether its right or wrong to use) you bet your bottom dollar they are working to fix it ASAP and will ban people for doing it for 'bug abuse'<br>
<br>
But is it not also 'bug abuse' to keep casting eye of zomm and drowning yourself?  Is it right that SOE only ban people for beneficial bug abuse?<br>
